{
  "number": 1639,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1639",
  "title": "Fix all broken links in the documentation",
  "body": "We have a lot of broken links in the documentation, mostly because we do things like `[/guide.html](guide)` and in production the real url is `/instantsearch.js/react/guide.html`.\r\n\r\nTwo ways to fix this:\r\n- use the [base href](https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/HTML/Element/base) attribute on the main webpage to define the base href for all relative (non http://) assets\r\n- try to use h.publicPath helper in markdown files (not sure this is doable)\r\n\r\nThe base href option seems to be a very convenient way to do what we want without having to use h.publicPath everywhere.",
